


translate English day6_my_rkn_ce7fd2b8:


    br "\n Maya Elbeth is an angel. {w}And I'll tell you why. {w}{nw}"


translate English day6_my_rkn_a209896c:


    extend "\n First of all, she's always looking down at the ground or up at the sky. Oh, and she hates standing against the wind."


translate English day6_my_rkn_8aacbcb0:


    extend "\n She hardly ever speaks up first, but always wants others to notice her. {w}{nw}"


translate English day6_my_rkn_2e15ef8b:


    extend "\n Her dainty fingertips are often covered in dirt or soot, and yet her fingernails, resembling tiny grains of rice, always smell like flowery soap. {w}{nw}"


translate English day6_my_rkn_04c9e8c7:


    extend "\n She never makes eye contact with other people for very long, but she always listens without interrupting, {w}no matter the nature of the conversation."


translate English day6_my_rkn_49f4e465:



    nvl clear
    br "\n She always has the same worried expression on her face, whether she's happy or sad. {w}And when holding back tears, she always squishes her mouth shut first."


translate English day6_my_rkn_76be76c1:


    extend "\n I know all this because I've been watching her this whole time. {w}She has no angel wings, at least none that human eyes can detect."


translate English day6_my_rkn_51c7d0e5:


    extend "\n I know that for a fact. {w}How, you might ask? Because I've seen her fly sometimes."


translate English day6_my_rkn_7228e30e:


    extend "\n A young girl trying to fly without wings would be a very sad sight indeed. Don't you agree?"


translate English day6_my_rkn_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day6_my_rkn_f6061251:


    nar "Maya stares at the flower bed, hugging her knees to her chest."


translate English day6_my_rkn_24254317:


    nar "When I get closer, I realize she's not looking at the flower beds--she's looking at her own fingers."


translate English day6_my_rkn_b3e55dff:


    nar "A row of black bugs are stuck to her slender digits."


translate English day6_my_rkn_2e44231b:


    nar "But she doesn't show any signs of disgust. In fact, she looks enraptured, as though looking at hundreds of tiny jewels."


translate English day6_my_rkn_5e3f5565:


    nar "I can't help but gasp. It's a shocking sight."


translate English day6_my_rkn_2a1ba27a:


    nar "As I awkwardly sit down, she suddenly notices my presence and turns toward me."


translate English day6_my_rkn_4c41fad5:


    nar "Our eyes meet and I struggle to calm my racing heart."


translate English day6_my_rkn_1cdffa21:


    pl "Good morning, Maya."


translate English day6_my_rkn_2fe1d178:


    my "Good morning, [na2]."


translate English day6_my_rkn_a4524bcf:


    nar "A thin smile comes over her face.{w} Hearing her voice calms my nerves and soothes my apprehension."


translate English day6_my_rkn_a0e47f55:


    pl "What are you doing...?"


translate English day6_my_rkn_106de017:


    my "Ah, they were here when I got here today.{w} I think they came from the roses..."


translate English day6_my_rkn_8c49f8ca:


    my "Maybe they needed a new home. Or maybe they got driven out by new life..."


translate English day6_my_rkn_66520213:


    pl "I mean, it's all growing outside, so one or two pests are bound to be here, but...{w} What are you doing with them?"


translate English day6_my_rkn_c8e0b217:


    my "I'm not really sure, but I feel like I have to make a decision."


translate English day6_my_rkn_4504d130:


    my "Whether I do something about it or not, one of the two will die."


translate English day6_my_rkn_c0efdb58:


    pl "Yeah, I guess you're right, but..."


translate English day6_my_rkn_4fffd129:


    my "You told me before that everything living has a set lifespan, right?"


translate English day6_my_rkn_e45d488d:


    my "Then maybe dying here is their fate."


translate English day6_my_rkn_65365980:


    pl "Maybe..."


translate English day6_my_rkn_701ad916:


    my "But... It's so sad to have to watch the sprouts I worked hard to grow die."


translate English day6_my_rkn_b3804ddb:


    nar "For some reason, she seems awfully skinny. It reminds me of my dream this morning.{w} A chill goes down my spine."


translate English day6_my_rkn_b4f4dd45:


    pl "Couldn't you just help them...?"


translate English day6_my_rkn_8b406e30:


    pl "I mean, I'm sure some people out there care about the rules of nature or whatever..."


translate English day6_my_rkn_f5fed90e:


    pl "But you worked hard raising those sprouts, right? It would be weird to just watch them die."


translate English day6_my_rkn_a2788be7:


    my "Oh. So that's how you think about it, [na2]..."


translate English day6_my_rkn_17b050ba:


    pl "I mean, not necessarily, in every case...{w} But when you're sad, I get sad too, you know."


translate English day6_my_rkn_6b40627d:


    nar "I hand Maya a handkerchief. She stares at it emptily as if she's never seen one before, but eventually takes it from me."


translate English day6_my_rkn_deb7080e:


    pl "I couldn't bear to watch, so I gave it to you because you have such a kind heart, Maya."


translate English day6_my_rkn_43613e49:


    my "I just don't know anything... Everything in my head feels all jumbled.{w} And while I watch, things... Things seem to get more complicated."


translate English day6_my_rkn_d3d01587:


    pl "Yeah, there are always times like that. When you focus on one thing for too long, you start overthinking it all,"


translate English day6_my_rkn_e5fb29f6:


    pl "and before you realize what's happening, you've already forgotten what the problem was to begin with."


translate English day6_my_rkn_a893972a:


    pl "It's called Gezuntight-fall or something complicated like that..."


translate English day6_my_rkn_7c16d8fd:


    my "Hey, [na2], do you remember what we talked about before?"


translate English day6_my_rkn_7f7e2522:


    pl "What was it?"


translate English day6_my_rkn_eb796d0f:


    my "...About the angel."


translate English day6_my_rkn_b47bc570:


    nar "My heart immediately sinks into my stomach."


translate English day6_my_rkn_8556a36e:


    pl "Yeah... I remember."


translate English day6_my_rkn_f25b222f:


    my "That stuff you said? I think you were right, [na2]..."


translate English day6_my_rkn_e375c1b0:


    my "When people or animals suddenly die or have some kind of unfortunate accident..."


translate English day6_my_rkn_e3e3e5ee:


    my "Their bad luck is nothing more than a product of karma."


translate English day6_my_rkn_91fae28d:


    pl "I mean, basically, yeah."


translate English day6_my_rkn_55f10a75:


    my "But there's no way I could ever know exactly what crimes I may have committed in a previous life, right? {w}It doesn't make sense..."


translate English day6_my_rkn_42d538c7:


    pl "I don't think it makes sense either.{w} Listen, Maya."


translate English day6_my_rkn_34a5539f:


    pl "I'm not sure why I'm telling you this, but at any rate, {w}where I come from, we're told that God has a reason for everything, even if it seems senseless at first."


translate English day6_my_rkn_afb8e2cf:


    pl "They'd often go on and on about this thing called \"karma,\" a mythical phenomenon that we have no way of proving truly exists."


translate English day6_my_rkn_62e7ff77:


    pl "It's just a fairy tale created by humanity to help explain things that don't make sense. {w}It's not something designed to torment yourself with."


translate English day6_my_rkn_e168caf9:


    my "Then why do animal, plants, and people die?"


translate English day6_my_rkn_bd15fca6:


    my "People usually blame misfortune on karma, and say that pestis is punishment. {w}And yet sometimes good people die tragic deaths while bad people live on seemingly forever..."


translate English day6_my_rkn_40a64476:


    nar "The very thought I'd try to avoid at all costs suddenly slaps me right in the face."


translate English day6_my_rkn_66dce5c9:


    pl "That's true. Hm... {w}How do I put this... {w}I don't think I've ever really thought that hard about why people die."


translate English day6_my_rkn_3676b09b:


    nar "One day, the time will come when we'll need to accept that even unfair deaths are meant to happen."


translate English day6_my_rkn_c8ce5d83:


    nar "Maya wipes off her bug-ridden hand.{w} That's all it takes for those little bugs to die."


translate English day6_my_rkn_47f4af12:


    nar "She hunches over a little, possibly thinking the same thing."


translate English day6_my_rkn_15499ddc:


    my "Dying is scary, huh?"


translate English day6_my_rkn_c25717ce:


    nar "I raise my hand and put it on her trembling shoulder as if comforting a child. Maya doesn't brush it away."


translate English day6_my_rkn_087b41ad:


    nar "Her curved back coils, as if trying to protect her frail body."


translate English day6_my_rkn_318ada70:


    nar "And I know that there are angel wings on it--I just can't see them."


translate English day6_my_rkn_dc5bb06a:


    pl "I'm pretty scared of you dying too, Maya..."


translate English day6_my_rkn_fea27462:


    nar "The voice, drowning in fear, breaks down into a hoarse moan. I feel a warmth in my hand from her back.{w} It's my voice."


translate English day6_my_rkn_810becc2:


    nar "But I'm not fearing my own death--I'm fearing Maya's eventual demise."


translate English day6_my_rkn_17000d4b:


    nar "Pestis is, for the most part, irrational, but is it not true that death comes first to those who've lost themselves along the way?"


translate English day6_my_rkn_46cf200b:


    nar "If Maya gives up on herself, then I'm afraid the person most at risk of getting infected by Pestis is her."


translate English day6_my_rkn_dee6e5f6:


    my "Hey, [na2]?"


translate English day6_my_rkn_ecd7ecdf:


    nar "As I'm about to lift my hand, she addresses me.{w} I start in surprise."


translate English day6_my_rkn_c7fcae0a:


    my "Did you... Did you talk to Cue about something before?"


translate English day6_my_rkn_c979a8b7:


    pl "H-Huh?!{w} Maya, you were watching?!"


translate English day6_my_rkn_1c95ae16:


    my "So you WERE talking...!"


translate English day6_my_rkn_fa3191e3:


    my "Cue has been kind of...{w} Well, kind of absent-minded, I guess. For a while, actually."


translate English day6_my_rkn_15200e8e:


    my "I got worried he had another fight with you."


translate English day6_my_rkn_dd85b480:


    pl "Oh...{w} No, no, we're not fighting anymore."


translate English day6_my_rkn_c7fa15c7:


    pl "It was starting to bother me too.{w} Are you maybe worried about something else?"


translate English day6_my_rkn_32ceefc5:


    my "Aren't you the one worried about something, [na2]?"


translate English day6_my_rkn_32ffc9f1:


    pl "Me? Wh-Why would you ask that?"


translate English day6_my_rkn_bbcc5f1b:


    my "Huh? I... I'm not really sure.{w} You said something weird before, didn't you?"


translate English day6_my_rkn_8d994408:


    pl "No, it... I just have a bunch of things on my mind. It's no big deal."


translate English day6_my_rkn_d2719f6b:


    my "It isn't?"


translate English day6_my_rkn_b854419d:


    nar "Maya stops talking again. I'm so afraid she'll suddenly disappear."


translate English day6_my_rkn_f2659fff:


    nar "It's just... I'm the only one who knows she's an angel. I thought I was the only one who could know her troubles and receive her favor."


translate English day6_my_rkn_ab58326c:


    nar "And she must know about that worry of mine."


translate English day6_my_rkn_b6e29f83:


    pl "Maya... What would you want me to do?"


translate English day6_my_rkn_dcfb65dc:


    my "Huh...?"


translate English day6_my_rkn_bb72a40a:


    pl "Do you want me to stay with you?{w} To protect you from the scary things?"


translate English day6_my_rkn_a8f8866a:


    pl "Or should I search for a way to make you happy?{w} I'd listen to any request you have of me."


translate English day6_my_rkn_72e67874:


    my "I..."


translate English day6_my_rkn_70ffe57c:


    nar "I finally start to understand why she's been listening to me talk about my worries this whole time.{w} She must want a promise from me. An oath."


translate English day6_my_rkn_004be379:


    nar "An oath that the happiness, the future, and the safety I've promised her won't end by a single moment of sincerity."


translate English day6_my_rkn_78f631c4:


    nar "An atonement, so to speak, for the promise that turned into a lie because I couldn't uphold it.{w} That's what Maya needs."


translate English day6_my_rkn_f3feed01:


    my "I guess I want you to honestly accept my help. That way, you'll be able to live without any worries at all, [na2]..."


translate English day6_my_rkn_eba3c34d:


    nar "Is she tired of seeing other people be unhappy?"


translate English day6_my_rkn_89324304:


    nar "Is that why she appears in my dreams every night?{w} Not to demand something of me, or seek my help, but to help me..."


translate English day6_my_rkn_dfe44cd1:


    nar "I blink slowly, looking at her face in profile.{w} She looks just like the girl I saw on the train that first day."


translate English day6_my_rkn_b3d2a3a1:


    pl "Thank you, Maya."


translate English day6_my_rkn_30743dfb:


    nar "She smiles at my belated expression of gratitude--a smile I couldn't have imagined the first day we met."


translate English day6_my_rkn_edc4eef4:


    nar "I take a seat across from her, then hear the bell announcing the lunch break."
